        "created_at": "2025-12-03T13:46:37.186Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hi everyone, I’m having an issue after switching from Android to iOS. I had an active Signal subscription on Android, and after transferring my account to my iPhone, Signal shows that I don’t have an active plan and asks me to pay again even though I already paid for this months active till dec 15. I cancelled the Android subscription only after transferring, as support instructed, but now iOS doesn’t recognize the existing payments asking to renew.</p>\n<p>I also need clarification about backups: I no longer using my Android cloud backup since account is not active there And is there any option for local backups on iOS like there is on Android?</p>\n<p>Support hasn’t replied to my recent emails, so I’m posting here in hopes of getting guidance. Thanks!</p>",
